gurmukhi: ਕ੍ਰਿਸ਼ਨ ਕ੍ਰਿਸ਼ਨ ਕਰਿ ਸਾਧ ਦੋ ਬਿਸ਼ਨ ਕ੍ਰਿਸ਼ਨ ਪਤਿ ਜਾਸ ॥ ਕ੍ਰਿਸ਼ਨ ਬਿਸ਼੍ਵ ਤਰਬੇ ਨਮਿਤ ਤਨ ਮੈ ਕਰਯੋ ਪ੍ਰਕਾਸ਼ ॥੫੬॥
transliteration: Krishan Krishan Kar(i) Saadh Do Bishan Krishan Pat(i) Jaas|| Krishan Bishav Tarbe Namit Tan Mai Daryo Prakaadh||56||
translation: Both Devaki and Vasudev, began to remember Vishnu, the lord of Lakshmi with extreme saintliness and here Vishnu entered and enlightened the body of Devaki in order to redeem the world darkened by vices.56.
Now begins the description about the Birth of Krishna

gurmukhi: ਸੰਖ ਗਦਾ ਕਰ ਅੳੁਰ ਤ੍ਰਿਸੂਲ ਧਰੇ ਤਨ ਕੳੁਚ ਬਡੇ ਬਡਭਾਗੀ ॥ ਨੰਦ ਗਹੈ ਕਰ ਸਾਰੰਗ ਸਾਰੰਗ ਪੀਤ ਧਰੈ ਪਟ ਪੈ ਅਨੁਰਾਗੀ ॥
transliteration: Sankh Gadaa Kar Aur Trisoo Ddare Tan Kaouch Bade Bade Badbhaagtee|| Nand Gadai Kar Saaran Saaran Peet Ddarai Pat Pai Anuraagee||
translation: Vishnu appeared in the womb of sleeping Devaki (in the form of Krishna) in yellow dress, wearing armour on body and holding conch, mace, trident, sword and bow in his hands;

gurmukhi: ਸੋੲੀ ਹੁਤੀ ਜਨਮਯੋ ੲਿਹ ਕੇ ਗ੍ਹਿ ਕੈ ਡਰਪੈ ਮਨ ਮੈ ੳੁਠ ਜਾਗੀ ॥ ਦੇਵਕੀ ਪੁਤ੍ਰ ਨ ਜਾਨਯੋ ਲਖਿਓ ਹਰਿ ਕੈ ਕੈ ਪ੍ਰਨਾਮ ਸੁ ਪਾੲਿਨ ਲਾਗੀ ॥੫੭॥
transliteration: Soihoutijanmyo Eh Ke Grah(i) Kaidarpai Man Mai Outh Jaagee|| Devakipoutra Na Jaanyo Lakhio Har(i) Kai Kai Pranaam Su Paain Laagee||57||
translation: Devaki was terrified, she awoke and sat down; she did not know that a son had been born to her; seeing Vishnu apparently, she bowed at his feet.57.

gurmukhi: ਲਖਯੋ ਦੇਵਕੀ ਹਰਿ ਮਨੈ ਲਖਯੋ ਨ ਕਰ ਕਰ ਤਾਤ ॥ ਲਖਯੋ ਜਾਨ ਕਰ ਮੋਹਿ ਕੀ ਤਾਨੀ ਤਾਨ ਕਨਾਤ ॥੫੮॥
transliteration: Lakhyo Devakihar(i) Manai Lakhyo Na Kar Kar Taat|| Lakhyo Jaan Kar Moh(i) Kitaanitaan Kanaat||58||
translation: Devaki did not consider him as a son, but saw him in the form of God, still, being a mother, her attachment grew.58.

gurmukhi: ਕ੍ਰਿਸ਼ਨ ਜਨਮ ਜਬ ਹੀ ਭਯੋ ਦੇਵਨ ਭਯੋ ਹੁਲਾਸ ॥ ਸ਼ਤ੍ਰ ਸਭੈ ਅਬ ਨਾਸ ਹੋਹਿ ਹਮ ਕੋ ਹੋੲਿ ਬਿਲਾਸ ॥੫੯॥
transliteration: Krishan Janam Joh Hibhayo Devan Bhayo Hulaas|| Shatra Sabhai Ab Naas Hoh(i) Ham Ko Hoe Bilaas||59||
translation: As soon as Krishna was born, the gods were filled with joy and thought that then the enemies would be destroyed and them they would be overjoyed.59.

gurmukhi: ਅਾਨੰਦ ਸੋਂ ਸਭ ਦੋਵਤਨ ਸੁਮਨ ਬਰਖਾੲਿ ॥ ਸ਼ੋਕ ਹਰਨ ਦੁਸ਼ਟਨ ਦਲਨ ਪ੍ਰਗਟੇ ਜਗ ਮੋ ਅਾੲਿ ॥੬੦॥
transliteration: Oonand Son Sabh Devtan Souman Barkhaae|| Shok Haran Doushtan Dalan Pragte Jag Mo Aae||60||
translation: Filled with delight, the gods showered flowers and believed that Vishnu, the destroyer of sorrows and tyrants had manifested himself in the world.60.

gurmukhi: ਜੈ ਜੈ ਕਾਰ ਭਯੋ ਜਬੈ ਸੁਨੀ ਦੇਵਕੀ ਕਾਨ ॥ ਤ੍ਰਾਸਤ ਹੁੲਿ ਮਨ ਮੈ ਕਹਿਯੋ ਸ਼ੋਰ ਕਰੈ ਕੋ ਅਾਨ ॥੬੧॥
transliteration: Jai Jai Kaar Bhayo Jabai Sounidevakikaan|| Traasat Hue Man Mai Kahiyo Shor Darai Ko Aan||61||
translation: When Devaki heard the hailings with her own ears, then she with fear began to think as to who was creating noise.61.

gurmukhi: ਬਾਸਦੇਵ ਅਰੁ ਦੇਵਕੀ ਮੰਤ੍ਰ ਕਰੈ ਮਨ ਮਾਹਿ ॥ ਕੰਸ ਕਸਾੲੀ ਜਾਨ ਕੈ ਹੀਅੈ ਅਧਿਕ ਡਰਪਾਹਿ ॥੬੨॥
transliteration: Baasdev Ar(u) Devakimantra Kari Man Maah(i)|| Kans Kasaaijaan Kai Heeai Adhik Darpaah(i)62||
translation: Vasudev and Devaki began to think between themselves and considering Kansa as a butcher, their hearts were filled with great fear.62.
End of the description about the Birth of Krishna.
